The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Ranbaxy profit up 20% at Rs 121 cr

 OUR BUREAU

 July 20: Ranbaxy Laboratories Ltd has posted a 19.54 per cent rise in profit after tax at Rs 121.1 crore for the quarter ended June 30 compared with Rs 101.3 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year on the back of robust sales in the US market.

 Consolidated sales increased to Rs 1,446.4 crore for the second quarter in 2006-07, up 7.3 per cent from Rs 1,347.9 crore in the corresponding quarter of 2005-06, the company said.

 For the six months ended June 30, the company reported a profit after tax of Rs 192.5 crore against Rs 172.1 crore a year ago. Sales for the January to June period rose to Rs 2,721.7 crore from Rs 2,486.2 crore during the same period last year.

 Raymond revenue 

 Raymond Limited recorded a 14 per cent increase in revenue at Rs 298.46 crore for the quarter ended June 30 compared with Rs 261.78 crore in the same quarter of the previous year. 

 The companys profit before tax and exceptional items was Rs 17.61 crore against Rs 26.90 crore in the same quarter last year. 

 The company claims that the dip in profit was due to the provision for diminution in the market value of its current investments and loss on translation of foreign exchange earnings in line with the accounting policies. 

 Gujarat Ambuja

 Gujarat Ambuja Cements Ltd (GACL) has reported better than expected numbers for the fourth quarter of the year ended June 30, 2006, with its net profit more than doubling to Rs 303.89 crore from Rs 145.17 crore a year ago.

 This 109 per cent jump in profits came on the back of a 57 per cent rise in net sales as cement prices remained firm during the quarter. 

 Net sales on a stand-alone basis rose to Rs 1,134.24 crore from Rs 720.52 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year.

 Godrej Consumer 

 Godrej Consumer Products has posted a net profit of Rs 30.49 crore for the first quarter ended June 30, an almost 13 per cent jump from Rs 27.12 crore in the same quarter last financial year. 

 Total income has increased from Rs 167.96 crore to Rs 192.40 crore, a jump of almost 15 per cent. 

 The group has posted a consolidated net profit of Rs 34.13 crore and the total income stood at Rs 238.44 crore. 




